      "text": "⇒ [[Identity]] enables us to accept the face we see in the [[Mirror]] as our own. We need it for coming to terms with the “grotesque mask” that we see there, which cannot be stripped away. We must identify with this face so that it does not appear to us as “an outrageous disguise,” or if so, then just for a moment. When we leave the bathroom, we need to trust that the image we project expresses our thoughts and feelings quite naturally, and we need to prepare ourselves for the fact that everyone else will take this face to be precisely who we are."
